post_text: Our first Virtual Teacher of the week is JoShawna Williams. Shout out to Ms. Williams for the amazing job she did this week. Williams uploaded all of her recorded lessons for each block in Google Classroom. She posted an agenda daily with objectives, standards, and the essential question. Ms. Williams used several different instructional strategies to keep students engaged throughout the lesson. She also found a creative way to incorporate classroom greeters virtually when administrators entered the google meet classroom. Williams has created a virtual learning environment that is full of energy and enthusiasm. She plays music as students enter the class; and she checks for understanding by allowing students to use white boards to reveal their answers, which is fun and interactive. Great job this week Ms. Williams, we appreciate the effort you put into meeting the expectations for virtual teaching! ~ Y‚Äôvonne Santos, Director of Learning

post_text: The time is here!!! Our first day of school is tomorrow. ALL students should report to school by 7:10am daily. ALL students must be appropriately dressed in their yellow CSAL polo style shirt and khaki bottoms. It is important for all students to be here on time. Upon dismissal, we are asking that all CSAL parents park on 16th street and wait in the carpool line. Once the last bus has pulled off, we will allow you to drive up to the school to pick up your child. Students WILL NOT be able to walk across the street to awaiting vehicles. We want to ensure ALL of our students are safe at all times. We are looking forward to serving you and our children this 2019-2020 school year. Again, WELCOME BACK CSAL FAMILY!!
